I have some urgent business.

429
00:17:33,020 --> 00:17:34,364
一切还好吧
Is everything all right?

430
00:17:34,375 --> 00:17:37,489
只是一个需要帮助的朋友
Oh, you know, just a, er, friend in need.

431
00:17:37,489 --> 00:17:39,625
天啊  什么朋友
Oh, dear. What friend?

432
00:17:40,385 --> 00:17:41,583
英格兰
England.

433
00:17:43,916 --> 00:17:47,687
还真是含糊
Well, that's not very specific.

434
00:17:51,083 --> 00:17:52,677
停尸房谁当班
Who's on mortuary duty?

435
00:17:54,020 --> 00:17:54,979
你知道的
You know who.

436
00:17:54,979 --> 00:17:56,385
总是他
Always him.

437
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:06,114
拜托告诉我是哪个傻瓜干的
Please tell me which idiot did this!

438
00:18:09,187 --> 00:18:11,302
这是为了大家的安全
It's for everyone's safety.

439
00:18:14,072 --> 00:18:16,791
这女人死了  她半边头都不见了
This woman is dead, half her head is missing.

440
00:18:16,791 --> 00:18:18,541
她对谁都不是威胁
She's not a threat to anyone.

441
00:18:18,697 --> 00:18:21,687
跟她的丈夫说去吧  他在那边的罩单下
Tell that to her husband, he's under a sheet over there.

442
00:18:21,687 --> 00:18:23,072
不管昨晚在莱姆豪斯发生了什么
Whatever happened in Limehouse last night,

443
00:18:23,072 --> 00:18:26,322
我们能断定那不是一个死去的女人干的
I think we can safely assume it wasn't the work of a dead woman.

444
00:18:26,739 --> 00:18:28,958
比这更奇怪的事都发生过
Stranger things have happened.

445
00:18:29,416 --> 00:18:30,593
比如呢
Such as...?

446
00:18:30,927 --> 00:18:34,072
奇怪的事
Well... Strange things.

447
00:18:34,072 --> 00:18:35,666
你说话跟小孩一样
You're speaking like a child.

448
00:18:35,666 --> 00:18:37,864
这显然是活人干的  他在哪里
This is clearly man's work. Where is he?

449
00:18:42,604 --> 00:18:43,656
福尔摩斯
Holmes.

450
00:18:45,895 --> 00:18:46,937
霍普
Hooper.

451
00:18:50,333 --> 00:18:52,468
你  继续工作
You, back to work!

452
00:18:53,729 --> 00:18:58,375
你是来用魔术震撼我们了吧
So, come to astonish us with your magic tricks, I suppose?

453
00:18:58,375 --> 00:19:00,625
你想提醒我注意什么事吗
Is there anything to which you would like to draw my attention?

454
00:19:00,625 --> 00:19:02,479
完全没有  福尔摩斯先生
Nothing at all, Mr Holmes.

455
00:19:03,250 --> 00:19:05,729
你想什么时候走都行
You may leave any time you like.

456
00:19:05,729 --> 00:19:09,291
霍普医生  是我请福尔摩斯先生来的  合作点
Dr Hooper, I asked Mr Holmes to come here. Cooperate.

457
00:19:09,291 --> 00:19:10,562
这是命令
That's an order.

458
00:19:13,208 --> 00:19:14,635
有两点"值得注意"
There are two "Features of interest",

459
00:19:14,635 --> 00:19:17,406
正如你在华生医生的故事里经常说的
as you are always saying in Dr Watson's stories.

460
00:19:17,406 --> 00:19:18,541
我从来没说过
I never say that.

461
00:19:18,541 --> 00:19:21,187
你说过  很多次
You do, actually, quite a lot.

462
00:19:22,312 --> 00:19:25,197
首先  这绝对是艾米丽娅・瑞克莱蒂
First of all, this is definitely Emelia Ricoletti.

463
00:19:25,197 --> 00:19:27,083
她已经被确定身份了
She has been categorically identified.

464
00:19:27,083 --> 00:19:28,322
这肯定是她  无可置疑
Beyond a doubt, it is her.

465
00:19:28,333 --> 00:19:30,343
那昨晚在莱姆豪斯是谁
Then who was that in Limehouse last night?

466
00:19:30,500 --> 00:19:32,458
也是艾米丽娅・瑞克莱蒂
That was also Emelia Ricoletti.

467
00:19:32,458 --> 00:19:34,989
不可能  她死了  躺在这里
It can't have been. She was dead, she was here.

468
00:19:35,614 --> 00:19:37,468
是她自己的丈夫
She was positively identified

469
00:19:37,468 --> 00:19:40,093
在死去的前几秒确认的
by her own husband, seconds before he died.

470
00:19:40,114 --> 00:19:42,968
他没理由撒谎  几乎不可能搞错
He had no reason to lie, could hardly have been mistaken.

471
00:19:42,968 --> 00:19:45,708
车夫也认识她  那就是她
The cabbie knew her, too, there's no question it's her.

472
00:19:45,864 --> 00:19:49,895
但她不可能同时出现在两个地方  对吧
But she can't have been in two places at the same time, can she?

473
00:19:49,979 --> 00:19:51,770
不  华生  对于刚死的人来说
No, Watson, one place is strictly the limit

474
00:19:51,770 --> 00:19:53,270
他们只能去一个地方
for the recently deceased.

475
00:19:53,562 --> 00:19:54,302
福尔摩斯
Holmes!

476
00:19:54,302 --> 00:19:56,354
-可能是双胞胎吗  -不
- Could it have been twins? - No.

477
00:19:56,541 --> 00:19:57,083
为什么
Why not?

478
00:19:57,093 --> 00:19:59,062
因为从来都不是双胞胎
Because it's never twins.

479
00:19:59,062 --> 00:20:01,343
艾米丽娅没有双胞胎  也没有姐妹
Emelia was not a twin, nor did she have any sisters.

480
00:20:01,343 --> 00:20:04,062
她有一个哥哥  四年前去世了
She had one older brother who died four years ago.

481
00:20:04,062 --> 00:20:07,968
也许是秘密的双胞胎
Hmm, maybe it was a secret twin.

482
00:20:08,510 --> 00:20:09,447
什么
A what?!

483
00:20:09,718 --> 00:20:11,729
秘密的双胞胎
A secret twin.

484
00:20:13,270 --> 00:20:14,208
知道吗
Hmm? You know?

485
00:20:14,208 --> 00:20:15,666
没人知道的双胞胎
A twin that nobody knows about.

486
00:20:15,666 --> 00:20:17,385
这一切可能是策划好的
This whole thing could have been planned.

487
00:20:17,875 --> 00:20:19,427
从怀孕时开始
Since the moment of conception.

488
00:20:19,427 --> 00:20:21,541
她真是太有先见之明了
How breathtakingly prescient of her.

489
00:20:21,541 --> 00:20:23,604
从来不是双胞胎  华生
It is never twins, Watson!

490
00:20:23,625 --> 00:20:24,760
那你怎么看
Then what's your theory?

491
00:20:25,666 --> 00:20:27,604
更重要的是  你什么毛病
More to the point, what's your problem?

492
00:20:28,583 --> 00:20:30,489
-我不明白  -你为什么这么害怕
- I, I don't understand... - Why were you so frightened?

493
00:20:30,489 --> 00:20:33,083
到现在为止  没什么能说明你为什么要喝酒
Nothing so far has justified your assault on my decanter,

494
00:20:33,083 --> 00:20:35,635
还有为什么允许一个死去的女人被逮捕
and why have you allowed a dead woman to be placed under arrest?

495
00:20:35,635 --> 00:20:38,697
因为还有一点"值得注意"
Ah, that would be the other feature of interest.

496
00:20:40,833 --> 00:20:43,187
她指尖上有一些血迹
A smear of blood on her finger.

497
00:20:43,291 --> 00:20:45,385
血迹的由来可以有多种解释
That could have happened any number of ways.

498
00:20:45,427 --> 00:20:46,645
没错
Indeed.

499
00:20:47,416 --> 00:20:48,854
还有一点
There's one other thing.

500
00:20:49,281 --> 00:20:51,072
之前没有血迹
It wasn't there earlier.

501
00:20:52,739 --> 00:20:54,656
那个也是新的
Neither was that.

502
00:21:04,562 --> 00:21:05,802
你
You!

503
00:21:06,072 --> 00:21:07,156
你
You?

504
00:21:08,041 --> 00:21:09,093
你
You?!

505
00:21:09,093 --> 00:21:10,125
福尔摩斯
Holmes?

506
00:21:12,520 --> 00:21:16,583
吞枪自尽  子弹贯穿头部...
Gun in the mouth, a bullet through the brain...

507
00:21:17,687 --> 00:21:20,927
后脑被轰掉
Back of the head blown clean off.

508
00:21:22,447 --> 00:21:24,812
他是怎么活下来的
How could he survive?

509
00:21:27,208 --> 00:21:28,614
你是说"她"吧
"She", you mean.

510
00:21:28,760 --> 00:21:29,614
什么
I'm sorry?

511
00:21:29,854 --> 00:21:32,135
不是"他"  是"她"
Not "He", "She".

512
00:21:32,218 --> 00:21:34,104
是  当然了
Yes, yes of course.

513
00:21:36,072 --> 00:21:38,604
谢谢你们给了我这么吸引人的案子
Well, thank you all for a fascinating case.

514
00:21:38,604 --> 00:21:41,447
我破案之后会给你们发电报的  华生
I'll send you a telegram when I've solved it. Watson.

515
