思维殿堂是一种记忆手段  我知道它的功用
The Mind Palace is a memory technique, I know what it can do

1228
01:04:05,989 --> 01:04:08,343
也知道它的局限
and I know what it most certainly cannot.

1229
01:04:08,854 --> 01:04:13,093
也许有那么一两件事  我知道而你不知道
Maybe there are one or two things that I know that you don't.

1230
01:04:13,500 --> 01:04:14,708
当然有了
Oh, there are.

1231
01:04:15,739 --> 01:04:17,145
你列了清单吗
Did you make a list?

1232
01:04:21,000 --> 01:04:22,000
你又胖了
You've put on weight.

1233
01:04:22,031 --> 01:04:23,531
马甲显然比外套新
That waistcoat is clearly newer than the jacket.

1234
01:04:23,531 --> 01:04:26,166
-别说了  你列清单了吗  -什么清单
- Stop this! Just stop it! Did you make a list?! - Of what?

1235
01:04:26,166 --> 01:04:28,291
所有的  夏洛克  你服的所有药物
Everything, Sherlock. Everything you've taken.

1236
01:04:28,291 --> 01:04:30,270
不  不是那样  他就是出神了
No, it's not that, he goes into a sort of trance.

1237
01:04:30,270 --> 01:04:31,250
我见过他那样做
I've seen him do it.

1238
01:04:42,010 --> 01:04:45,312
从那天起  弟弟和我达成了协议
We have an agreement, my brother and I, ever since that day.

1239
01:04:48,552 --> 01:04:49,781
不管在哪里找到他
Wherever I find him,

1240
01:04:50,760 --> 01:04:53,479
背街小巷也好  小客栈也罢
whatever back alley or doss-house...

1241
01:04:54,729 --> 01:04:56,552
一定要有张清单
..There will always be a list.

1242
01:04:57,260 --> 01:04:59,437
他不可能在五分钟内服这么多
He couldn't have taken all that in the last five minutes.

1243
01:05:00,875 --> 01:05:02,541
他上飞机前就嗨了
He was high before he got on the plane.

1244
01:05:02,541 --> 01:05:04,010
看起来不像
He didn't seem high.

1245
01:05:04,125 --> 01:05:06,656
瘾君子最能骗人
Nobody deceives like an addict.

1246
01:05:06,666 --> 01:05:08,489
我不是瘾君子  我只是服用药物
I'm not an addict, I'm a user.

1247
01:05:08,958 --> 01:05:10,312
减缓我无聊的情绪
I alleviate boredom and

1248
01:05:10,312 --> 01:05:12,895
或者偶尔提高我的思考效率
occasionally heighten my thought processes.

1249
01:05:12,895 --> 01:05:14,708
老天  这可能要了你的命
For God's sake! This could kill you!

1250
01:05:14,708 --> 01:05:17,770
-你可能会死  -控制剂量就不会致命
- You could die! - Controlled usage is not usually fatal

1251
01:05:17,770 --> 01:05:20,312
节制的生活也不能永生
and abstinence is not immortality.

1252
01:05:20,312 --> 01:05:21,281
你在做什么
What are you doing?

1253
01:05:21,281 --> 01:05:23,166
艾米丽娅・瑞克莱蒂  我在搜她
Emelia Ricoletti, I'm looking her up.

1254
01:05:23,864 --> 01:05:25,375
好吧  也许是应该看看
Oh, I suppose we should.

1255
01:05:25,583 --> 01:05:28,510
我有权查询军情五处的最高机密资料库
I have access to the top level of the MI5 archive.

1256
01:05:28,510 --> 01:05:30,145
对  我正在那儿搜索
Yep, that's where I'm looking.

1257
01:05:31,677 --> 01:05:34,250
你认为军情五处的防火墙怎么样
What do you think of MI5 security?

1258
01:05:35,093 --> 01:05:37,375
弄一个也挺好的
I think it would be a good idea.

1259
01:05:38,416 --> 01:05:40,562
艾米丽娅・瑞克莱蒂  "悬案"
Emelia Ricoletti, "Unsolved",

1260
01:05:40,979 --> 01:05:41,833
跟他说的一样
like he says.

1261
01:05:41,833 --> 01:05:43,562
你们能不能闭嘴五分钟
Could you all just shut up for five minutes!

1262
01:05:43,562 --> 01:05:44,802
我必须回去
I have to go back.

1263
01:05:44,989 --> 01:05:45,750
我就快破案了
I was nearly there before

1264
01:05:45,750 --> 01:05:47,666
结果让你们跑进来吵没了
you stepped on and started yapping away!

1265
01:05:47,666 --> 01:05:50,250
吵  抱歉  我们是打扰你治疗了吗
"Yapping?" Sorry, did we interrupt your session?

1266
01:05:50,479 --> 01:05:51,677
夏洛克  听我说
Sherlock, listen to me.

1267
01:05:51,677 --> 01:05:53,156
不想听  你越说越来劲
No, it only encourages you.

1268
01:05:53,156 --> 01:05:55,281
-我没生你的气  -我真松了口气啊
- I'm not angry with you. - Oh, that's a relief!

1269
01:05:55,281 --> 01:05:57,802
我本来还一直担心呢  不  等等
I was really worried... No, hold on,

1270
01:05:57,802 --> 01:05:58,937
我真没担心
I really wasn't.

1271
01:06:00,093 --> 01:06:01,687
我以前救过你
I was there for you before.

1272
01:06:02,458 --> 01:06:04,010
下一次我还会救你
I'll be there for you again.

1273
01:06:06,406 --> 01:06:08,218
不论多少次我都会救你
I'll always be there for you.

1274
01:06:10,489 --> 01:06:11,770
这是我的错
This was my fault.

1275
01:06:12,770 --> 01:06:14,406
这与你无关
It was nothing to do with you.

1276
01:06:15,218 --> 01:06:16,458
入狱一周
A week in a prison cell,

1277
01:06:16,458 --> 01:06:18,437
-我该意识到的  -意识到什么
- I should have realised. - Realised what?

1278
01:06:18,708 --> 01:06:19,593
对你来说
That, in your case,

1279
01:06:19,604 --> 01:06:23,010
单独监禁其实是和死敌关在一起
solitary confinement is locking you up with your worst enemy.

1280
01:06:23,010 --> 01:06:24,468
我的神啊
Oh, for God's sake!

1281
01:06:24,729 --> 01:06:26,010
吗啡还是可卡因
Morphine or cocaine?

1282
01:06:28,729 --> 01:06:29,843
你说什么
What did you say?

1283
01:06:30,343 --> 01:06:31,520
我什么也没说
I didn't say anything.

1284
01:06:31,802 --> 01:06:33,000
不  你说了  你说
No, you did, you said...

1285
01:06:33,802 --> 01:06:36,406
今天是什么  吗啡还是可卡因
Which is it today? Morphine or cocaine.

1286
01:06:39,572 --> 01:06:40,406
福尔摩斯
'Holmes?'

1287
01:06:40,572 --> 01:06:42,989
吗啡还是可卡因  今天是什么
Morphine or cocaine - which is it today?

1288
01:06:43,843 --> 01:06:45,364
回答我  该死的
Answer me, damn it!

1289
01:06:47,052 --> 01:06:48,531
莫里亚蒂来过
Moriarty was here.

1290
01:06:49,562 --> 01:06:50,666
莫里亚蒂死了
Moriarty's dead.

1291
01:06:53,604 --> 01:06:54,989
我刚刚在飞机上
I was on a jet.

1292
01:06:55,791 --> 01:06:56,697
什么上
A what?

1293
01:06:56,812 --> 01:06:58,625
你也在  还有麦考夫
You were there, and Mycroft.

1294
01:06:59,625 --> 01:07:01,593
你就没出过门  福尔摩斯
You haven't left these rooms, Holmes.

1295
01:07:02,781 --> 01:07:05,656
连动都没动一下
You...haven't...moved.

1296
01:07:05,822 --> 01:07:08,583
告诉我  是吗啡还是可卡因
Now, tell me, morphine or cocaine?

1297
01:07:10,156 --> 01:07:13,416
可卡因  7%的
Cocaine. A 7% solution.

1298
01:07:14,406 --> 01:07:15,895
-想来点吗  -不想
- Would you care to try it? - No.

1299
01:07:16,177 --> 01:07:18,364
但我十分想把这儿所有的
But I would quite like to find every ounce of the stuff

1300
01:07:18,364 --> 01:07:20,229
这破玩意儿都找到然后倒窗外
in your possession and pour it out of the window.

1301
01:07:20,906 --> 01:07:22,375
那我会想阻止你
I should be inclined to stop you.

1302
01:07:22,375 --> 01:07:25,385
那我将用强有力的方式提醒你
Then you would be reminded, quite forcibly,

1303
01:07:25,583 --> 01:07:28,687
我们两个中谁是军人  谁是瘾君子
which of us is a soldier and which of us a drug addict.

1304
01:07:28,958 --> 01:07:31,114
你不是军人  你是个医生
You're not a soldier, you are a doctor.

1305
01:07:31,114 --> 01:07:32,614
我是个军医  也就是说我可以
I'm an army doctor, which means I could break

1306
01:07:32,614 --> 01:07:34,979
在掰断你每一根骨头时顺便叫出它的学名
every bone in your body while naming them.

1307
01:07:35,302 --> 01:07:39,625
亲爱的华生  你的感情干扰了你的判断
My dear Watson, you are allowing emotion to cloud your judgment.

1308
01:07:39,635 --> 01:07:40,750
办案不吸毒
Never on a case.

1309
01:07:41,656 --> 01:07:43,385
你保证过的  办案不吸毒
You promised me, never on a case.

1310
01:07:43,385 --> 01:07:45,083
不  那是出自
No, I just said that

1311
01:07:45,083 --> 01:07:46,645
-你的一篇故事  -听着
- in one of your stories. - Listen,

1312
01:07:47,552 --> 01:07:49,718
我很乐意为你扮演捧哏
I'm happy to play the fool for you.

1313
01:07:49,802 --> 01:07:52,687
我可以笨蛋一样跟着你到处跑
I will run along behind you like some halfwit,

1314
01:07:52,687 --> 01:07:54,562
衬托出你的聪明  如果你需要如此
making you look clever, if that's what you need.

1315
01:07:54,562 --> 01:07:56,416
但看在上帝分上
But dear God above,

1316
01:07:56,562 --> 01:07:59,791
你得给自己定个更高的标准
you will hold yourself to a higher standard!

1317
01:07:59,791 --> 01:08:02,020
-为什么  -因为人们需要你
- Why? - Because people need you to.

1318
01:08:02,020 --> 01:08:04,208
什么人  为什么  就因为你的蠢故事
What people, why? Because of your idiot stories?

1319
01:08:04,208 --> 01:08:06,760
没错  就因为我的蠢故事
Yes, because of my "Idiot stories".

1320
01:08:06,947 --> 01:08:08,135
福尔摩斯先生
Mr Holmes!

1321
01:08:09,343 --> 01:08:11,781
福尔摩斯先生  电报  福尔摩斯先生
Mr Holmes, telegram, Mr Holmes.

1322
01:08:20,427 --> 01:08:21,677
怎么了  出什么事了
What is it? What's wrong?

1323
01:08:22,677 --> 01:08:25,208
-是玛丽  -玛丽  她怎么了
- It's Mary. - Mary? What about her?

1324
01:08:25,208 --> 01:08:27,447
-她很有可能陷入了危险  -危险
- It's entirely possible she's in danger. - Danger?

1325
01:08:27,447 --> 01:08:28,812
一刻也不能耽误了
There's not a moment to lose.

1326
01:08:29,468 --> 01:08:31,479
这是你吸毒的幻觉吗
Is this the cocaine talking?

1327
01:08:32,000 --> 01:08:33,125
玛丽能有什么危险
What danger could Mary be in?

1328
01:08:33,125 --> 01:08:36,229
-她肯定只是去拜访朋友了  -快走
- I'm sure she's just visiting with friends. - Come on!

1329
01:08:42,031 --> 01:08:43,500
到底怎么了
What is happening?

1330
01:08:43,583 --> 01:08:45,437
你这状况真的可以吗
Are you even in a fit state?

1331
01:08:45,927 --> 01:08:48,552
为玛丽当然可以  这毋庸置疑  华生
For Mary, of course. Never doubt that, Watson.

1332
01:08:49,614 --> 01:08:50,666
毋庸置疑
Never that.

1333
01:08:51,864 --> 01:08:52,770
福尔摩斯
Holmes?

1334
01:08:53,010 --> 01:08:54,187
我没事  我没事
I'm fine. I'm fine!

1335
01:08:56,083 --> 01:08:57,437
别戴那顶
Not that one!

1336
01:08:58,781 --> 01:08:59,614
戴这顶
This one.

1337
01:09:00,635 --> 01:09:02,260
-为什么  -你是夏洛克・福尔摩斯
- Why? - You're Sherlock Holmes.

1338
01:09:02,260 --> 01:09:03,468
戴你该戴的帽子吧
Wear the damn hat.

1339
01:09:10,822 --> 01:09:13,062
出租马车  马车
Cab! Cab!

1340
01:09:16,239 --> 01:09:17,927
说吧  她在哪
So tell me, where is she?

1341
01:09:18,635 --> 01:09:20,822
告诉我  到底是怎么回事
You must tell me, what's going on?!

1342
01:09:20,822 --> 01:09:21,927
我的好华生啊
Oh, good old Watson!

1343
01:09:21,927 --> 01:09:24,416
你不问问题我们这些闲暇时间该怎么过啊
How would we fill the time if you didn't ask questions?!

1344
01:09:24,416 --> 01:09:27,104
夏洛克  快告诉我  我妻子在哪
Sherlock, tell me where my bloody wife is,

1345
01:09:27,104 --> 01:09:28,156
你这个自大的混蛋
you pompous prick,

1346
01:09:28,156 --> 01:09:29,750
否则我真跟你动手
or I'll punch your lights out!

1347
01:09:31,520 --> 01:09:32,864
福尔摩斯  她在哪
Holmes, where is she?

1348
01:09:34,781 --> 01:09:36,364
一个废弃教堂
A de-sanctified church.

1349
01:09:36,364 --> 01:09:37,885
她觉得她找到了答案
She thinks she's found the solution and,

1350
01:09:37,885 --> 01:09:39,062
也正因此
for no better reason than that,

1351
01:09:39,062 --> 01:09:41,562
她让自己陷入了巨大的危险
she's put herself in the path of considerable danger.

1352
01:09:42,135 --> 01:09:43,760
这妻子真是选的好啊
What an excellent choice of wife.

1353
01:09:56,802 --> 01:09:58,010
搞什么
What the devil?!

1354
01:09:58,093 --> 01:09:59,218
我找到他们了
I've found them.

1355
01:10:08,177 --> 01:10:09,145
这是什么啊  玛丽
What is all this, Mary?

1356
01:10:09,145 --> 01:10:11,354
是一切的核心  约翰
This is the heart of it all, John.

1357
01:10:11,416 --> 01:10:13,062
阴谋的核心
The heart of the conspiracy.

1358
01:10:33,562 --> 01:10:36,291
神啊  这是什么地方啊
Great God, what is this place?

1359
01:10:36,979 --> 01:10:38,708
而且你又来这儿干什么
And what the devil are you doing here?!

1360
01:10:38,708 --> 01:10:40,614
我一直在调查
I've been making enquiries.

1361
01:10:41,156 --> 01:10:42,947
应福尔摩斯先生之请
Mr Holmes asked me.

1362
01:10:43,052 --> 01:10:44,156
福尔摩斯  你怎么能这么做
Holmes, how could you?

1363
01:10:44,156 --> 01:10:46,270
不  不是他  聪明的那位
No, not him, the clever one.

1364
01:10:46,906 --> 01:10:47,916
我认为很明显
It seemed obvious to me

1365
01:10:47,916 --> 01:10:50,427
这件事一个人无法完成
that this business could not be managed alone.

1366
01:10:50,427 --> 01:10:53,312
我认为瑞克莱蒂太太有帮手
My theory is that Mrs Ricoletti had help.

1367
01:10:53,312 --> 01:10:54,770
她的朋友
Help from her friends.

1368
01:10:54,916 --> 01:10:57,625
-漂亮  玛丽  "聪明的那位"  -我
- Bravo, Mary. "The clever one?" - I...

1369
01:10:58,166 --> 01:11:00,083
我以为我要失去你了
I thought I was losing you.

1370
01:11:01,250 --> 01:11:03,104
我以为我们
I thought perhaps we were...

1371
01:11:03,708 --> 01:11:05,864
-在冷战  -是你先搬出去的
- neglecting each other. - Well, you're the one who moved out.

1372
01:11:05,875 --> 01:11:08,020
我是在跟玛丽说话
I was talking to Mary.

1373
01:11:09,114 --> 01:11:10,635
你怎么为麦考夫办事了
You're working for Mycroft?

1374
01:11:10,812 --> 01:11:12,916
他想监督他的疯弟弟
He likes to keep an eye on his mad sibling.

1375
01:11:12,916 --> 01:11:15,447
而且手头正好有间谍  你从来没发现
And he had a spy to hand. Has it never occurred to you

1376
01:11:15,447 --> 01:11:17,541
你妻子的能力远超普通护士吗
your wife is excessively skilled for a nurse?

1377
01:11:17,541 --> 01:11:18,572
他当然没发现
Of course it hasn't,

1378
01:11:18,760 --> 01:11:21,197
因为他知道护士该有的能力
because he knows what a nurse is capable of.

1379
01:11:21,218 --> 01:11:22,427
你又是什么时候发现的
When did it occur to you?

1380
01:11:22,427 --> 01:11:23,739
刚发现  不好意思
Only now, I'm afraid.

1381
01:11:23,791 --> 01:11:25,250
肯定很痛苦吧
Must be difficult,

1382
01:11:25,500 --> 01:11:27,208
当天才的笨弟弟
being the slow little brother.

1383
01:11:27,208 --> 01:11:29,697
也该跟上节奏了  聊够了  办正事
Time I sped up. Enough chatter, let's concentrate.

1384
01:11:29,875 --> 01:11:32,625
好吧  这是干什么
Yes, all right. What's all this about?

1385
01:11:33,250 --> 01:11:34,562
他们想做什么
What do they want to accomplish?

1386
01:11:34,562 --> 01:11:36,177
进去弄个明白吧
Why don't we go and find out.

1387
01:11:55,541 --> 01:11:57,583
抱歉  见到锣不敲就难受
Sorry! I can never resist a gong.

1388
01:11:57,583 --> 01:12:00,031
-少了戏剧性也难受  -谁能想到呢
- Or a touch of the dramatic. - Never have guessed!

1389
01:12:00,614 --> 01:12:03,822
你们好像跟我一样  喜欢戏剧性
Though it seems you share my enthusiasm in that regard.

1390
01:12:05,500 --> 01:12:06,635
真棒
Excellent.

1391
01:12:07,187 --> 01:12:08,937
一流的剧场
Superlative theatre.

1392
01:12:09,697 --> 01:12:12,072
场面令人赞叹
I applaud the spectacle.

1393
01:12:15,250 --> 01:12:16,791
艾米丽娅・瑞克莱蒂饮弹自尽
Emelia Ricoletti shot herself,

1394
01:12:16,791 --> 01:12:20,458
然后起死回生  杀死了她丈夫
then apparently returned from the grave and killed her husband.

1395
01:12:20,864 --> 01:12:21,822
那么...
So...

1396
01:12:22,739 --> 01:12:23,927
是怎么回事呢
how was it done?

1397
01:12:24,958 --> 01:12:26,906
按时间顺序回顾一下吧
Let's take the events in order.

1398
01:12:29,958 --> 01:12:31,989
瑞克莱蒂太太用最快的速度
Mrs. Ricoletti gets everyone's attention

1399
01:12:31,989 --> 01:12:34,104
-吸引了所有人的注意力  -你
- in very efficient fashion. - You!

1400
01:12:37,125 --> 01:12:38,156
你
You?!

1401
01:12:38,760 --> 01:12:39,843
还是我
Or me?

