Will you help me?

1572
01:21:38,927 --> 01:21:40,395
{\an3}法国谚语
原意是如果一个男人行为怪异
就"去找到在与他偷情的女人吧"

1573
01:21:38,927 --> 01:21:40,395
找到这个女人吧
Cherchez la femme.

1574
01:22:26,416 --> 01:22:27,479
上帝啊
Oh, dear.

1575
01:22:28,333 --> 01:22:29,833
不在里面
The cupboard is bare.

1576
01:22:31,885 --> 01:22:33,437
肯定埋在下面了
They must have buried it underneath.

1577
01:22:34,062 --> 01:22:36,343
肯定埋在棺材下面了
They must have buried it underneath the coffin.

1578
01:22:51,281 --> 01:22:52,781
不走运  夏洛克
Bad luck, Sherlock.

1579
01:22:55,031 --> 01:22:57,145
也许他们用其他方式处理了尸体
Maybe they got rid of the body in another way.

1580
01:22:57,145 --> 01:22:58,718
-不  -很有可能
- No... - More than likely.

1581
01:22:58,854 --> 01:23:00,729
毕竟这是很久之前的事了
At any rate, it was a very long time ago.

1582
01:23:00,729 --> 01:23:04,062
而我们可还有更重要的事需要办  弟弟
We do have slightly more pressing matters to hand, little brother.

1583
01:23:04,395 --> 01:23:06,687
莫里亚蒂  死而复生
Moriarty? Back from the dead?

1584
01:23:06,687 --> 01:23:10,187
别忘了我
'Do not forget me.

1585
01:23:11,104 --> 01:23:15,447
别忘了我
'Do not forget me!'

1586
01:23:29,864 --> 01:23:30,770
这是
This?

1587
01:23:31,593 --> 01:23:32,916
我明白了
Oh, I see.

1588
01:23:34,572 --> 01:23:36,427
还是没醒  是吗
Still not awake, am I?

1589
01:24:03,927 --> 01:24:06,281
太深了  夏洛克  太深了
Too deep, Sherlock, way too deep.

1590
01:24:07,364 --> 01:24:09,906
恭喜  你将是史上第一个被活埋在
Congratulations, you will be the first man in history

1591
01:24:09,906 --> 01:24:12,708
自己的思维殿堂里的人
to be buried in his own Mind Palace.

1592
01:24:14,708 --> 01:24:17,343
场景布置的有点夸张了  你不觉得吗
The setting is a shade melodramatic, don't you think?

1593
01:24:17,489 --> 01:24:18,572
对你我而言
For you and me?

1594
01:24:20,166 --> 01:24:21,166
一点都不夸张
Not at all.

1595
01:24:24,364 --> 01:24:25,614
你到底是什么
What are you?

1596
01:24:26,500 --> 01:24:27,864
你知道我是什么
You know what I am.

1597
01:24:28,552 --> 01:24:29,875
我是莫里亚蒂
I'm Moriarty.

1598
01:24:30,416 --> 01:24:32,302
犯罪界的拿破仑
The Napoleon of Crime.

1599
01:24:32,302 --> 01:24:34,791
-莫里亚蒂已经死了  -在你脑中可没有
- Moriarty's dead! - Not in your mind.

1600
01:24:34,791 --> 01:24:36,583
在你脑中我永远都不会死
I'll never be dead there.

1601
01:24:37,187 --> 01:24:39,958
你曾说你的大脑是块硬盘
You once called your brain a hard drive.

1602
01:24:40,104 --> 01:24:42,322
跟病毒打个招呼吧
Well, say hello to the virus.

1603
01:24:43,000 --> 01:24:45,104
这就是我们的结局  你和我
This is how we end, you and I.

1604
01:24:46,000 --> 01:24:47,229
总是在这里
Always here,

1605
01:24:48,135 --> 01:24:49,489
总是你和我一起
always together.

1606
01:24:51,989 --> 01:24:55,093
你的脑子很不错  莫里亚蒂
You have a magnificent brain, Moriarty.

1607
01:24:55,427 --> 01:24:56,791
我很敬佩
I admire it.

1608
01:24:57,406 --> 01:25:00,760
我认为它甚至可能与我相当
I concede it may even be the equal of my own.

1609
01:25:01,177 --> 01:25:02,291
我很感动
I'm touched.

1610
01:25:04,989 --> 01:25:06,093
我很荣幸
I'm honoured.

1611
01:25:06,666 --> 01:25:09,145
但说到在悬崖边缘
But when it comes to the matter of unarmed combat

1612
01:25:09,156 --> 01:25:11,156
徒手搏斗
on the edge of a precipice...

1613
01:25:12,718 --> 01:25:14,406
你等着入水吧
You're going in the water,

1614
01:25:15,302 --> 01:25:17,010
小个子
short-arse.

1615
01:25:29,718 --> 01:25:32,593
你觉得自己高大威猛吗  夏洛克
Oh, you think you're so big and strong, Sherlock!

1616
01:25:32,593 --> 01:25:33,802
在我面前可不是
Not with me.

1617
01:25:47,572 --> 01:25:49,500
我是你的弱点
I am your weakness!

1618
01:25:51,697 --> 01:25:53,072
我能打倒你
I keep you down!

1619
01:25:54,822 --> 01:25:58,572
每次你失足  每次你失败
Every time you stumble, every time you fail,

1620
01:25:58,791 --> 01:26:00,447
每当你势弱
when you're weak,

1621
01:26:00,572 --> 01:26:02,270
我都
I...am...

1622
01:26:03,020 --> 01:26:03,979
在那儿
there!

1623
01:26:06,781 --> 01:26:07,645
不
No,

1624
01:26:08,270 --> 01:26:09,677
别抵抗
don't try to fight it.

1625
01:26:09,895 --> 01:26:11,864
躺好  认输吧
Lie back and lose!

1626
01:26:17,697 --> 01:26:19,354
我们一起跳下去吧
Shall we go over together?

1627
01:26:20,208 --> 01:26:21,947
必须是我们一起  是吧
It has to be together, doesn't it?

1628
01:26:21,947 --> 01:26:24,812
到最后  永远是你
At the end it's always just you

1629
01:26:25,343 --> 01:26:26,718
和我
and me!

1630
01:26:32,927 --> 01:26:35,354
教授  麻烦你离我朋友远点
Professor, if you wouldn't mind stepping away from my friend,

1631
01:26:35,354 --> 01:26:39,531
我相信  他有点反感你的纠缠
I do believe he finds your attention a shade annoying.

1632
01:26:41,843 --> 01:26:43,666
这不公平  你们二对一
That's not fair, there's two of you!

1633
01:26:44,927 --> 01:26:47,343
我们总是两个人  你不看《斯特兰德月刊》吗
There's always two of us. Don't you read The Strand?

1634
01:26:49,447 --> 01:26:51,062
跪下  教授
On your knees, Professor.

1635
01:26:55,562 --> 01:26:58,468
手背到头后
Hands behind your head.

1636
01:26:59,208 --> 01:27:00,302
谢谢你  约翰
Thank you, John.

1637
01:27:02,604 --> 01:27:04,125
你什么时候开始叫我约翰了
Since when do you call me John?

1638
01:27:05,406 --> 01:27:06,822
你肯定想不到
You'd be surprised.

1639
01:27:07,062 --> 01:27:08,083
未必
No, I wouldn't.

1640
01:27:11,031 --> 01:27:12,583
你该醒来了  夏洛克
Time you woke up, Sherlock.

1641
01:27:14,760 --> 01:27:16,916
我是个讲故事的  我分得出自己是在故事里
I'm a story-teller, I know when I'm in one.

1642
01:27:17,375 --> 01:27:18,489
当然
Of course.

1643
01:27:19,302 --> 01:27:20,895
当然了  约翰
Of course you do, John.

1644
01:27:21,812 --> 01:27:22,937
他什么样
So what's he like?

1645
01:27:23,739 --> 01:27:26,166
另一个世界的我
The other me in the other place?

1646
01:27:27,187 --> 01:27:28,822
比看上去聪明
Smarter than he looks.

1647
01:27:29,083 --> 01:27:30,520
那一定很聪明了
Pretty damn smart, then.

1648
01:27:31,989 --> 01:27:33,395
很聪明
Pretty damn smart.

1649
01:27:33,479 --> 01:27:37,187
你俩直接私奔得了
Ugh, why don't you two just elope, for God's sake?!

1650
01:27:37,562 --> 01:27:38,833
无礼
Impertinent.

1651
01:27:39,656 --> 01:27:40,760
过分
Offensive.

1652
01:27:40,989 --> 01:27:43,552
其实  你介意吗
Actually, would you mind?

1653
01:27:43,843 --> 01:27:44,854
完全不
Not at all.

1654
01:27:54,979 --> 01:27:56,875
-本来就该我了  -是啊
- It was my turn. - Quite so.

1655
01:27:57,645 --> 01:27:59,729
你打算怎么醒过来
So how do you plan to wake up?

1656
01:28:03,187 --> 01:28:04,552
就这样吧
I should think like this.

1657
01:28:06,520 --> 01:28:07,447
你确定吗
Are you sure?

1658
01:28:08,437 --> 01:28:11,239
偷偷告诉你  约翰  坠落是杀不死我的
Between you and me, John, I always survive a fall.

1659
01:28:11,781 --> 01:28:12,635
可你是怎么做到
But how?

1660
01:28:14,614 --> 01:28:16,479
很简单的  亲爱的华生
Elementary, my dear Watson.

1661
01:28:49,958 --> 01:28:51,895
-想我了吗  -夏洛克  你没事吧
- Miss me? - Sherlock, are you all right?

1662
01:28:51,895 --> 01:28:53,677
是的  当然  我怎么会有事呢
Yes. Of course I am, why wouldn't I be?

1663
01:28:53,677 --> 01:28:56,020
因为你可能刚服药过量  你该入院
Because you probably just OD'd. You should be in hospital.

1664
01:28:56,020 --> 01:28:57,239
没时间了
Hm, no time.

1665
01:28:57,968 --> 01:29:00,687
我得赶紧去贝克街  莫里亚蒂回来了
I have to go to Baker Street now, Moriarty's back.

1666
01:29:01,302 --> 01:29:03,041
我都希望他是真回来了
I almost hope he is,

1667
01:29:03,791 --> 01:29:05,364
如果能让你不再沉迷于此
if it'll save you from this.

1668
01:29:07,677 --> 01:29:09,010
现在用不着这个了
No need for that now,

1669
01:29:09,718 --> 01:29:10,760
我有真正好玩的了
I've got the real thing.

1670
01:29:10,760 --> 01:29:12,979
-我有工作了  -夏洛克
- I have work to do. - Sherlock...

1671
01:29:14,500 --> 01:29:15,520
保证我
..Promise me.

1672
01:29:17,750 --> 01:29:19,041
你还站这儿干什么
What are you still doing here?

1673
01:29:19,041 --> 01:29:21,020
你不是该去帮我搞个赦免还是什么的吗
Shouldn't you be off getting me a pardon or something,

1674
01:29:21,020 --> 01:29:22,604
像个好大哥那样
like a proper big brother?

1675
01:29:28,322 --> 01:29:29,406
华生医生
Dr Watson...

1676
01:29:34,052 --> 01:29:35,187
照顾好他
Look after him.

1677
01:29:37,072 --> 01:29:37,916
拜托
Please.

1678
01:29:59,812 --> 01:30:01,395
夏洛克  等等  解释一下
Sherlock, hang on, explain.

1679
01:30:01,666 --> 01:30:02,937
莫里亚蒂还活着吗
Moriarty's alive, then?

1680
01:30:02,937 --> 01:30:05,260
我没说他活着  我说他回来了
I never said he was alive, I said he was back.

1681
01:30:05,354 --> 01:30:06,531
那么他死了吗
So he's dead?

1682
01:30:06,697 --> 01:30:07,385
他当然死了
Of course he's dead,

1683
01:30:07,385 --> 01:30:09,604
他开枪爆了自己的头  不可能活下来
he blew his own brains out, no-one survives that.

1684
01:30:10,156 --> 01:30:12,635
我刚刚为了证明这点而服药过量
I just went to the trouble of an overdose to prove it.

1685
01:30:13,781 --> 01:30:16,697
莫里亚蒂死了  毫无疑问
Moriarty is dead, no question.

1686
01:30:17,843 --> 01:30:22,010
但更重要的是  我很清楚他接下来要做什么
But more importantly, I know exactly what he's going to do next.

1687
01:30:32,635 --> 01:30:33,875
飞行机
Flying machines,

1688
01:30:33,875 --> 01:30:36,239
还有什么...电话
these, er, telephone contraptions?

1689
01:30:36,250 --> 01:30:38,291
这是什么疯狂的幻想啊
What sort of lunatic fantasy is that?

1690
01:30:38,291 --> 01:30:39,406
只是我对
It was simply my conjecture

1691
01:30:39,406 --> 01:30:40,958
未来世界
of what a future world might look like

1692
01:30:40,968 --> 01:30:43,489
和你我在其中角色的猜想
and how you and I might fit inside it.

1693
01:30:43,875 --> 01:30:45,989
一个逻辑学家应该可以从一滴水
From a drop of water a logician should be able to infer

1694
01:30:45,989 --> 01:30:48,593
推断出是大西洋还是尼亚加拉河
the possibility of an Atlantic or a Niagara.

1695
01:30:48,593 --> 01:30:50,031
或是莱辛巴赫瀑布
Or a Reichenbach?

1696
01:30:50,343 --> 01:30:53,000
-你把这桩案子写好了吗  -是的
- Have you written up your account of the case? - Yes.

1697
01:30:54,416 --> 01:30:55,541
经过修改把它写成了
Modified to put it down as

1698
01:30:55,541 --> 01:30:58,333
-罕见的我未能破案的案例了吧  -当然
- one of my rare failures, of course? - Of course.

1699
01:31:01,635 --> 01:31:03,093
《无形军队
The Adventure Of...

1700
01:31:03,593 --> 01:31:05,156
历险记》
The Invisible Army.

1701
01:31:06,958 --> 01:31:08,343
或者愤怒军团
The League Of Furies?

1702
01:31:09,406 --> 01:31:10,958
恐怖军团
The Monstrous Regiment?

1703
01:31:11,333 --> 01:31:14,864
我倒想起名为《恐怖新娘》
I rather thought The Abominable Bride.

1704
01:31:15,697 --> 01:31:17,208
-有点庸俗  -但会畅销的
- A trifle lurid. - It'll sell.

1705
01:31:17,208 --> 01:31:18,854
而且还包含了正式八经的谋杀
It's got proper murders in it too.

1706
01:31:18,854 --> 01:31:20,072
你是这方面的专家嘛
You're the expert.

1707
01:31:20,083 --> 01:31:22,322
至于你的故事
As for your own tale,

1708
01:31:23,593 --> 01:31:27,270
你还确定你只用了7%的溶剂吗
are you sure it's still just a 7% solution that you take?

1709
01:31:27,270 --> 01:31:29,562
我觉得你是不是调高用量了
I think you may have increased the dosage.

1710
01:31:29,572 --> 01:31:31,552
或许我是有点异想天开了
Perhaps I was being a little fanciful.

1711
01:31:32,854 --> 01:31:35,541
但或许  这种事真的会发生
But perhaps such things could come to pass.

1712
01:31:36,906 --> 01:31:39,531
不管怎样  我相信我在那个世界会很自在的
In any case, I know I would be very much at home in such a world.

1713
01:31:39,531 --> 01:31:42,458
-我看我不会的  -我不敢苟同
- Huh, I don't think I would be. - I beg to differ.

1714
01:31:44,218 --> 01:31:46,843
但我一向知道自己是个先于时代之人
But then I've always known I was a man out of his time.


